"title": "2206: Jesus, the Christ",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2206: jesus, the christ",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>“Christ” means “Messiah” or “anointed one”. As the Christ, Jesus is the one who fulfils all OT expectations. Paul's phrase “in Christ” indicates the intimate relationship between Jesus Christ and his people.</p>\n<h2>The Christ as the anointed one</h2>\n<h3>The act of anointing in the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:13</a></strong> <em>Anointing symbolises God's calling and being equipped by his Spirit.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:15\">EXO 40:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:12\">LEV 8:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:1\">1SA 10:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:39\">1KI 1:39</a></p>\n<h3>Anointed OT leaders</h3>\n<p>Priests:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:7\">EXO 29:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:3\">LEV 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:5\">LEV 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:20\">LEV 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:32\">LEV 16:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:6\">1SA 24:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:10\">1SA 24:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:9\">1SA 26:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:11\">1SA 26:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:16\">1SA 26:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:23\">1SA 26:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:50\">PSA 18:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps20:6\">PSA 20:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:10\">PSA 132:10</a></p>\n<h3>The OT promise of a future anointed leader</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:1-Isa11:2\">ISA 11:1–11:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1\">ISA 42:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5-Jer23:6\">JER 23:5–23:6</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus' own claims to be the Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:25-John4:26\">JHN 4:25–4:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:10\">MAT 23:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:63-Matt26:64\">MAT 26:63–26:64</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:61-Mark14:62\">MRK 14:61–14:62</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:24-John10:25\">JHN 10:24–10:25</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus recognised as the Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:16\">MAT 16:16</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:29\">MRK 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:20\">LUK 9:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:26-Luke2:32\">LUK 2:26–2:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:41\">LUK 4:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:41-John1:42\">JHN 1:41–1:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:27\">JHN 11:27</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus' demand that his identity as the Christ should not be publicised</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:20\">MAT 16:20</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:30\">MRK 8:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:21\">LUK 9:21</a> <em>Jesus' reluctance to be known as the Christ is probably due to Jewish misunderstandings of the Messiah's true role.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:16\">MAT 12:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:41\">LUK 4:41</a></p>\n<h2>Grounds for affirming Jesus as the Christ</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's birth in Bethlehem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:4-Matt2:6\">MAT 2:4–2:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:2\">MIC 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:4-Luke2:7\">LUK 2:4–2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's spiritual anointing from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:38\">ACT 10:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:16\">MAT 3:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:10\">MRK 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:34\">JHN 3:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:27\">ACT 4:27</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's proclamation of Jubilee</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:17-Luke4:21\">LUK 4:17–4:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:2\">ISA 61:1–61:2</a> <em>Isaiah's words are borrowed from the language of the Year of Jubilee (Leviticus chapter 25), which was to be a time when true freedom was restored.</em></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's healing ministry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:16-Matt8:17\">MAT 8:16–8:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:4\">ISA 53:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:2-Matt11:5\">MAT 11:2–11:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:18-Luke7:23\">LUK 7:18–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:31\">JHN 7:31</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's prophetic ministry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:29\">JHN 4:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:45-Matt21:46\">MAT 21:45–21:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:67-Matt26:68\">MAT 26:67–26:68</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:19\">JHN 4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:26\">JHN 7:26</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's suffering, death and resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:26\">LUK 24:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:46\">LUK 24:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:18\">ACT 3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:3\">ACT 17:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:23\">ACT 26:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:11\">1PE 1:11</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's fulfilment of prophecy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:20\">2CO 1:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:22-Matt1:23\">MAT 1:22–1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14\">ISA 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:21-Matt26:24\">MAT 26:21–26:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:18-Mark14:21\">MRK 14:18–14:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps41:9\">PSA 41:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:4-Matt21:7\">MAT 21:4–21:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:14-John12:15\">JHN 12:14–12:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:9\">ZEC 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:8-Matt21:9\">MAT 21:8–21:9</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:9-Mark11:10\">MRK 11:9–11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:37-Luke19:38\">LUK 19:37–19:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:12-John12:13\">JHN 12:12–12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:26\">PSA 118:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:22-Acts2:36\">ACT 2:22–2:36</a></p>\n<h3>God's establishment of Jesus Christ as king</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32-Luke1:33\">LUK 1:32–1:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:6-Ps2:7\">PSA 2:6–2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6\">ISA 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:29\">LUK 22:29</a></p>\n<h2>Messianic titles used of Jesus</h2>\n<h3>Son of David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:1\">MAT 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22\">MAT 15:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:9\">MAT 21:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:30-Matt20:31\">MAT 20:30–20:31</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:47-Mark10:48\">MRK 10:47–10:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:38-Luke18:39\">LUK 18:38–18:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:8\">2TI 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Son of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:33\">MAT 14:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:54\">MAT 27:54</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:39\">MRK 15:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:34\">JHN 1:34</a></p>\n<h3>The Prophet</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:11\">MAT 21:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:14\">JHN 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:40\">JHN 7:40</a></p>\n<h3>King of the Jews</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:2\">MAT 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:37\">MAT 27:37</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:26\">MRK 15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:38\">LUK 23:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:19\">JHN 19:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:32\">MRK 15:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:13\">JHN 12:13</a></p>\n<h3>High priest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:17\">HEB 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14-Heb4:15\">HEB 4:14–4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:5\">HEB 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:20\">HEB 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1\">HEB 8:1</a></p>\n<h2>Israel's rejection of Jesus as the Christ</h2>\n<h3>Jesus' messiahship was largely rejected by the Jews</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:22\">MAT 27:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:11\">JHN 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:13\">JHN 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:37\">JHN 11:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:52-Acts7:53\">ACT 7:52–7:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:3-Acts17:5\">ACT 17:3–17:5</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus was accused of blasphemy because of his claims to be the Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:61-Mark14:64\">MRK 14:61–14:64</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:63-Matt26:66\">MAT 26:63–26:66</a></p>\n<h2>That Jesus is the Christ is a central Christian belief</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:31\">JHN 20:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:27\">JHN 11:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:1\">1JN 5:1</a></p>\n<h2>The apostles' message was that Jesus is the Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:42\">ACT 5:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:36\">ACT 2:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:22\">ACT 9:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:38\">ACT 10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:5\">ACT 18:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:28\">ACT 18:28</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is the representative head of the church</h2>\n<h3>Baptism is into Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:27\">GAL 3:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38\">ACT 2:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:48\">ACT 10:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:3\">ROM 6:3</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ lives within believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:8\">ROM 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1\">ROM 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:7\">ROM 16:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13\">EPH 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1\">COL 3:1</a></p>",
